        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2018-06-11 15:31:05.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 5:\n\nHi Nokia team, thank you for the contribution.\nI'm out of office until Friday, will be able review it early next week.\n - Thanks and apologies for the delay.",
        "patchset_number": 5
      },
      {
        "id": "9b0b09447cfc4252f226413e17b76189531feb5b",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 3663,
          "name": "Tomasz Golabek",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "tomasz.golabek@nokia.com",
          "username": "golabek"
        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2018-06-14 07:39:03.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 5:\n\n(4 comments)",
        "patchset_number": 5
      },
      {
        "id": "bc65db030d268ecb822c3fc487cc8a438424bc5e",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 3663,
          "name": "Tomasz Golabek",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "tomasz.golabek@nokia.com",
          "username": "golabek"
        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2018-06-14 08:18:12.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 5:\n\nGenerally VID makes a lot of external calls to other components APIs do i would like to use additional rest client like unirest.io rather then JAX-RS. We could remove huge part of this client-creation helpers etc. What do You think?",
        "patchset_number": 5
      },
      {
        "id": "c4bef71b446ab50a231318a7e2e8b54e2eb76876",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 653,
          "name": "Ofir Sonsino",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "ofirson@gmail.com",
          "username": "os0695"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2018-06-18 11:02:05.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 5:\n\nI never got to work with unirest, is it flexible enough in your opinion? \nIf we go that path, maybe it's worth making some research for more rest client libraries. Basically less code would be easier to maintain so I think it's a good idea.",
        "patchset_number": 5
      },
      {
        "id": "0928f7f2e7ddb51343f8388d16dad3eb07734f0e",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 3663,
          "name": "Tomasz Golabek",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "tomasz.golabek@nokia.com",
          "username": "golabek"
        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2018-06-18 13:47:36.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 5:\n\n> I never got to work with unirest, is it flexible enough in your\n > opinion?\n > If we go that path, maybe it's worth making some research for more\n > rest client libraries. Basically less code would be easier to\n > maintain so I think it's a good idea.\n\n\nWe can choose few to check, but this unirest seems to be a good choice. Not sure how to compare it with other frameworks cause it shoudnt have any performance impact. Only one thing we could measure is how complicated code will be at the end of the implementation...I have some additional things to ask so lets discuss it via email, ok?",
        "patchset_number": 5
      },
      {
        "id": "3d6f0db434003221a5e74807495b4f2812fa46cb",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 653,
          "name": "Ofir Sonsino",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "ofirson@gmail.com",
          "username": "os0695"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2018-06-19 10:31:52.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 5:\n\nGladly.\nAs for the +2, tomorrow I'll review it with the rest of the team, we have refactored this code area too in ECOMP version of VID so we will have to merge those eventually (that's why it takes longer). Thanks",
        "patchset_number": 5
      },
      {
        "id": "2c2b2188318c6dfa196dae95c82f4c2cd5ee57a1",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 653,
